b. tribunus plebis. Flaminius had been tribunus plebis in B.e. 232, when, in spite of the opposition of the Senate, he had carried an agrarian law sor the distribution of the Ager Picenus conquered from the Gauls.

c. qui abrogabatur, “which was attempted to be an- nulled.'' Flaminius was elected consul in 223, and set out for the war against the Gauls. The Optimates declared the election invalid, on account of a defect in the auspiceS, and sent to recall him. But Flaminius engaged the enemy and gained a complete victory. After his triumph he laid down his office, but it is not certain whether he was obliged to do so by his adversaries, or whether his time of office had expired.
